benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/catalog/simplePlan - Add a simple plan entry in the current version of the catalog

covered: Valid Payload: Scenarios @TC01, @TC02, @TC12, @TC13, @TC19, @TC20, @TC21, @TC23, @TC24 cover successful creation with valid data.
Invalid Payload: @TC04, @TC05, @TC09, @TC18 cover malformed JSON, missing required fields, and invalid data.
Duplicate Submission: @TC06 covers conflict when planId exists.
Missing Headers: @TC03 covers missing X-Killbill-CreatedBy header.
Extra Fields: @TC07 covers unsupported fields in the request.
Empty Request Body: @TC08 covers empty payload handling.
Service Unavailability: @TC11, @TC24 cover catalog service down or degraded states.
Maximum/Minimum Values: @TC12, @TC13 cover boundary testing for field lengths and values.
Unsupported HTTP Method: @TC14 covers method not allowed.
Large Payloads: @TC15 covers very large data submissions.
System Recovery: @TC16 covers retries after network failures.
Response Time: @TC17 covers performance within threshold.
Add when catalog is empty or partially populated: @TC19, @TC20.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover handling of large datasets requiring pagination.
Authorization: No explicit tests for invalid or expired tokens beyond missing header.
Rate Limiting: No tests simulate rapid repeated requests to test throttling.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios test for cache headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Timeouts: No tests simulate server timeouts or delayed responses.
Soft Deletes or Versioning: No tests cover soft delete behavior or version conflicts.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination to verify correct handling of large datasets.
Include tests for authorization with invalid or expired tokens.
Implement rate limiting tests to ensure system handles request bursts.
Add scenarios to verify caching headers and cache invalidation.
Simulate server timeouts and delayed responses to test resilience.
Test soft delete or version conflict scenarios if applicable.
